A widow whose husband was shot dead by her pastor lover has admitted to plotting the murder.

Teresa Stone, 40, will be sentenced in June after pleading guilty on Monday to conspiracy to commit murder in the March 2010 death of Randy Stone of Independence, Missouri.

Prosecutors say she conspired with her minister, David Love, who is serving a life prison sentence after admitting last year that he shot Randy Stone to death.

