In a self-help manual, Mr Stone listed Love as the most influential person in his life, and he sometimes attended weekly counselling sessions with him.

Mr Stone was active at the church and Love gave his eulogy, saying: 'We sit here and we weep not just because of the separation from our loved one, but because of all the questions that death brings, questions like "Why? Why him? Why now?",' according to a report early this year in The Kansas City Star.

